==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: differentiated
<hw>differentiated</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>made different
(especially in the course of development) or shown to be different;
<as>as, the <ex>differentiated</ex> markings of butterflies; the
<ex>regionally</ex> differentiated results</as>. Opposite of
<ant>undifferentiated</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>exhibiting biological
specialization; adapted during development to a specific function or
environment; <as>as, <ex>differentiated</ex> cells</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>differential</ent>⟦br⟧
